<p>A reverse option could be handy. All the motor controllers and many sensors already have that. Wouldn’t hurt to include it for non-motor controller usage.</p>
<p>Including a kS static amount that barely does not make the plant move and follows the sign of the output is useful. I coded essentially the same wrapper this morning and included those two functions. The WPILib feed forward has the kS but it doesn’t follow the sign of the error only.</p>
<p>Your incremental amounts for the gains should be settable variables and default to 0.  They are a couple of orders of magnitude larger than what I was tuning today and would have destroyed the machine.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":22,"updated_at":"2024-04-09T02:13:56.270Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":252,"readers_count":251,"score":55.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":461838,"topic_slug":"pidlib","display_username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":58360,"username":"Mateo","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/f4b2a3/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":24594,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pidlib/461838/6","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3355959,"name":"","username":"Mateo","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/f4b2a3/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-09T03:05:15.816Z","cooked":"<p>hmm those are good ideas! how would i implement the backwards thing? and do you think what i have so far would work?</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":22,"updated_at":"2024-04-09T03:05:15.816Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":223,"readers_count":222,"score":49.6,"yours":false,"topic_id"