ar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/slab-mr.thomas/{size}/182153_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-09T15:11:19.625Z","cooked":"<p>This helps you <a href="https://docs.revrobotics.com/rev-hardware-client/ion/telemetry#tuning" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Telemetry Tab | REV Hardware Client</a> and for your drivetrain it looks like <code>SysId</code> is the tool to use.</p>
<p>I don’t think you indicated swerve drive or not and what are you using for the <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controller - WPILib, SparkMax internal? Note that the WPILib swerve uses a Profiled Controller for the steer motors which you are not covering in your code. The drive is plain <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span>.</p>
<p>You don’t show how you terminate your iterative process of searching for gains but I’d bet you need a really long hallway if you are just going to start and wait a while for the tune to end. And you’ll need to be steering the robot while tuning so it doesn’t crash into the side walls.</p>
